This collection curates, modernizes, and re-packages n8n workflow templates
from the open-source community. Those templates are distributed under the MIT
License by their respective authors, and their original rights are retained.

Community sources this collection draws from include:
  - The official n8n community workflow library (https://n8n.io/workflows)
  - Zie619/n8n-workflows (MIT)
  - enescingoz/awesome-n8n-templates (MIT)
  - felipfr/awesome-n8n-workflows (MIT)

The curation, quality auditing, security sanitization, modernization to current
n8n nodes and AI models, categorization, and documentation in this repository
are original work by the maintainer and are likewise released under the MIT
License (see LICENSE).

If you are the author of a workflow included here and would like different
attribution or removal, please open a private security advisory or contact the
maintainer, and it will be addressed promptly.
